    <part id="apis-and-ai">
      <title>APIs and AI: It's complicated</title>
      <slide id="ai-success">
        <title>AI Success Stories</title>
        <img src="cover-state-of-ai-in-business-2025.png" href="https://nanda.media.mit.edu/ai_report_2025.pdf" title='Aditya Challapally, Chris Pease, Ramesh Raskar, and Pradyumna Chari, "The GenAI Divide: State of AI in Business 2025", MIT NANDA, July 2025' style=" height : 70% ; float: left ; margin : 0% 4% 4% 4% ; " class="shadow" />
        <img src="cover-state-of-ai-2025.png" href="https://www.mckinsey.com/capabilities/quantumblack/our-insights/the-state-of-ai" title='Alex Singla, Alexander Sukharevsky, Lareina Yee, and Michael Chui, "The state of AI in 2025: Agents, innovation, and transformation", McKinsey, November 2025' style=" height : 70% ; margin : 0% 4% 4% 4% ; " class="shadow" />
      </slide>
      <slide id="api-ai-new-york">
        <title>(How) does AI affect APIs?</title>
        <img src="apis-and-ai-cover.jpg" title="How does AI affect APIs? Expert Opinions from API Days New York 2025" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=6ekEQR45IIo" class="fullsize-shadow"/>
      </slide>
      <slide id="audience-poll">
        <title>Let's See Where We Are… ✋</title>
        <ol>
          <li>Who has <em>all/most/many APIs described</em> with OpenAPI/AsyncAPI?</li>
          <li>Who has a <em>central API catalog</em> or portal?</li>
          <li>Who can <em>track every API call</em> with full observability?</li>
          <li>Who has <em>sandbox environments</em> with synthetic data?</li>
          <li>Who has <em>AI agents working with APIs in production?</em></li>
        </ol>
        <hr />
        <ul>
          <li>Don't worry if you didn't raise your hand much</li>
          <li>Start with the basics, build incrementally</li>
        </ul>
      </slide>
      <slide id="api-landscape-lifecycle">
        <title>The API Landscape Lifecycle</title>
        <ul>
          <li>Not about single APIs → It's about the API landscape</li>
          <li>Lifecycle of evolving towards AI readiness</li>
          <ol>
            <li><link href="tool-availability"/></li>
            <li><link href="tool-description"/></li>
            <li><link href="tool-search"/></li>
            <li><link href="workflow-tools"/></li>
            <li><link href="tool-practices"/></li>
          </ol>
        </ul>
      </slide>
      <slide id="bridging-the-gap">
        <title>Bridging the Gap Between API Land and AI Land</title>
        <img src="golden-path-guardrail.webp" title="Golden Path with a Guardrail" style="float: right ; height : 72% ; margin : 0% 4% 4% 4% ; "/>
        <ul>
          <li>API landscapes are not AI-ready yet</li>
          <li>Descriptions and designs often make AI difficult</li>
          <li><q>Letting AI agents loose</q> oftentimes is not an option</li>
          <ul>
            <li><em>Limit blast radius:</em> Only provide access through a centralized access point</li>
            <li><em>Zero tolerance:</em> Never allow access to production APIs</li>
          </ul>
          <li>Use AI <em>as much as necessary</em> but <em>as little as possible</em></li>
        </ul>
      </slide>
    </part>
    <part id="tool-availability">
      <title>More Tools</title>
      <slide id="api-access-matters">
        <title>Why More APIs Matter</title>
        <img src="workbench.jpg" class="fullsize-shadow" />
